# Workspace Rules & Conventions

## Directory Structure
- `/public`: Final assets (SVG/PNG) for Slidev.
- `/tex`: LaTeX source files for TikZ/PGFPlots diagrams.
- `/scripts`: Python scripts for generating complex mathematical plots.

## Slidev Image Handling
- **HTML Tags**: Prefer `<img>` over Markdown syntax for precise layout control.
  - Example: `<img src="/plot.svg" class="h-80 mx-auto" alt="Description" />`
- **SVG Rendering**: Convert LaTeX to SVG using `dvisvgm --no-fonts`. This ensures math symbols are rendered as paths for perfect browser compatibility.

## Plot Design
- Prefer using tex for plots

## Technical Accuracy (Circuit Analysis)
- **Simple Pole**: -20 dB/decade slope; phase shift $0^\circ \to -90^\circ$.
- **Simple Zero**: +20 dB/decade slope; phase shift $0^\circ \to +90^\circ$.
- **Complex Zero Pair**: +40 dB/decade slope; correction factor **$+20 \log_{10}(2\zeta)$**.
- **Complex Pole Pair**: -40 dB/decade slope; correction factor **$-20 \log_{10}(2\zeta)$** (Resonant Peak for small $\zeta$).

## Text Formatting
- Use \LaTeX for math
- the sub-quesion "(c)" should be written as "\(c\)"   